      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_InvoiceSummary_Export",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve and export a summary of invoice data from a SQL Server database. It allows filtering based on various parameters such as invoice ID, provider ID, group ID, fiscal year, contract ID, billing period, date range, and status ID. The procedure constructs a query to fetch invoice details and related information from views, formats the data, and returns it in a structured format."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
